<task id="R2-011" project="SprkChat Platform Enhancement R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Document Context Injection Service — Conversation-Aware Semantic Chunking with 30K Token Budget</title>
    <status>pending</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, document-intelligence</tags>
    <estimated-effort>large</estimated-effort>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF API code implementation — creates a new DocumentContextService class with complex AI logic (embedding similarity, chunk selection, token budget management); critical for FR-02 and FR-03; downstream tasks R2-012 and R2-013 depend on this class</rigor-reason>
    <dependencies>[006]</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create a new class `DocumentContextService` in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/` that
    injects source document content into SprkChat conversations within a 30K token budget using
    conversation-aware semantic chunking.

    **Class design** (factory-instantiated, NOT DI-registered per ADR-010):
    ```csharp
    public class DocumentContextService
    {
        public DocumentContextService(SpeFileStore speFileStore, SemanticDocumentChunker chunker,
            IChatClient embeddingClient, IDistributedCache cache) { ... }

        public Task&lt;DocumentContextResult&gt; InjectDocumentContextAsync(
            string sessionId, string documentId, IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatMessage&gt; chatHistory,
            CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);
    }
    ```

    **Behavior**:
    1. Retrieve document binary from `SpeFileStore.GetFileAsync(documentId)` using the facade (not Graph SDK)
    2. Extract text via `SemanticDocumentChunker` (or appropriate existing text extraction service) — produces
       a list of `DocumentChunk` records with text, token count, and position metadata
    3. If total document tokens &lt;= 30K: inject all chunks verbatim into the system prompt section
    4. If total document tokens &gt; 30K (conversation-aware re-selection):
       a. Generate an embedding for the latest user message in `chatHistory`
       b. Score each chunk by cosine similarity to the latest message embedding
       c. Select top-N chunks that fit within the 30K token budget (greedy by similarity score)
       d. Include positional context header ("Showing sections most relevant to your question...")
    5. Return `DocumentContextResult` containing: selected chunks, total tokens used, whether truncation occurred
    6. Integrate with `PlaybookChatContextProvider` — the context provider calls `InjectDocumentContextAsync`
       and appends the selected chunks to the document context section of the system prompt

    **Data governance**: MUST NOT log chunk text content per ADR-015. Log only metadata: document ID,
    total chunks, selected chunk count, token budget used.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with Azure AI and Minimal API expertise</role>

  <goal>
    `DocumentContextService` exists in `Services/Ai/Chat/`, is factory-instantiated by `SprkChatAgentFactory`,
    correctly retrieves document content via `SpeFileStore`, performs conversation-aware chunk selection within
    the 30K token budget, and integrates with `PlaybookChatContextProvider` to inject chunks into the system
    prompt. AI can answer questions about document content without the user pasting text (FR-02). Asking about
    different document sections in sequence surfaces the relevant section content (FR-03).
  </goal>

