    <patterns>
      <pattern>Factory instantiation: SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools() uses `new ServiceClass(dep1, dep2)` with dependencies resolved from IServiceProvider — follow this exact pattern for DocumentContextService</pattern>
      <pattern>Cosine similarity for chunk selection: embed the latest user message, compute dot product against pre-computed chunk embeddings, sort descending, select greedy until token budget exhausted</pattern>
      <pattern>Token counting: use existing token counting utility in the codebase (check TextExtractionService or a TokenCounter helper) rather than creating a new one</pattern>
      <pattern>PlaybookChatContextProvider integration: the context provider builds a system prompt string — append document chunks to the "document context" section following the existing 8K playbook context section</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      SprkChat R1 could only reason about content the user explicitly pasted into the chat. R2 introduces
      automatic document context injection: when a session opens with a document ID (from AnalysisWorkspace),
      `DocumentContextService` retrieves the document, chunks it, and injects the most relevant sections into
      the system prompt. The 30K token budget is the document's allocation within the overall 128K context
      window — it leaves room for playbook context (8K), conversation history, and the model's response.

      Conversation-aware re-selection (FR-03) means that after each user message, the service re-evaluates
      which document chunks are most relevant to the conversation so far. This adds per-turn latency but
      dramatically improves accuracy for long documents where the user asks about different sections in sequence.

      `SemanticDocumentChunker` or an equivalent text extraction service should already exist in
      `Services/Ai/TextExtraction/` — use it rather than re-implementing chunking logic. If it does not
      exist, create a minimal wrapper around Document Intelligence's chunking output.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Depends on Task R2-006 (Phase 1 deployment). Safe to run in parallel with R2-010, R2-013, R2-014,
      R2-015 through R2-019. Task R2-012 depends on this task (multi-document extends DocumentContextService).
      Task R2-013 (document upload) calls DocumentContextService after extraction. Own files:
      `Services/Ai/Chat/DocumentContextService.cs` and `Models/Ai/Chat/DocumentContextResult.cs`.
    </dependencies>
  </context>

